ETL_MAPPING_QUERY_DESC: This is the SQL query to be run at the source. This forms the Extract section of the ETL module. The output of this query is saved under the variable rows and passed to the transform template for transformation. This field is used to test the mapping.
ETL_MAPPING_TRANSFORM_DESC: The Transformation template. Uses Velocity Syntax. This field is used to test the mapping.
ETL_MAPPING_CRON_DESC: Optional CRON expression used to run this mapping regularly on a scheduled basis.
ETL_MAPPING_FETCH_SIZE_DESC: This is the fetch size parameter to retrieve the data in chunks.
ETL_MAPPING_LOAD_DESC: The Load template. Uses Velocity Syntax. Has access to both the extracted data and transformed data. Typically uses Spring services to load data into this OpenMRS installation.
ETL_MAPPING_TEST_RESULTS_SIZE_DESC: Number of test results to be displayed.
ETL_MAPPING_TEST_BUTTON_TOOLTIP_ENABLED: Only Extract and Transform can be tested.
ETL_MAPPING_TEST_BUTTON_TOOLTIP_DISABLED: The entity must be saved before testing.
ETL_MAPPING_TEST_PARSE_FAILURE: Unable to display mapping testing result
ETL_DELETE_MAPPING_DESCRIPTION: Are you sure you want to delete this Mapping?
ETL_DELETE_DATABASE_DESCRIPTION: Are you sure you want to delete this Database?
